The lafinancepourtous.com site is published by the Institute for Public Financial Education (IEFP), an association of general interest, eligible for sponsorship and approved by the Ministry of National Education.

The IEFP was created to help everyone acquire the knowledge bases necessary to:
• Feel more comfortable with financial matters;
• Understand the economic issues of the world in which we live;
• Make fully informed decisions that concern us.

Our goals

As part of its educational and informative vocation, the Institute has set four priorities:
• Encourage financial education at school;
• Promote training in the company on the main subjects in personal finance (budget, financial check-up, employee savings, credit, relationship with your bank, etc.);
• Inform consumers of financial products;
• Help people in financial difficulty by relying on relay associations.

The IEFP wishes to contribute to the development of proactive financial education accessible to all by giving French people the necessary knowledge bases to enable them to:
• Better manage their money
• Becoming aware of the usefulness of a budget, knowing how to construct and manage it, is important, even and especially for those who have limited means. The budget is the key to your personal finances;
• Better understand and choose financial products;
• Feel more comfortable in their daily environment.

Financial Education, Training, and Budget

