This association aims to:
Bring together French structures whose purpose is to run, primarily or incidentally, an open manufacturing space (FabLab), participating in the international network of “FabLabs”;
Represent its members before public authorities and administrations as well as other organizations in Europe and around the world;
Provide support, advice and support to its members;
Communicate on the actions, achievements and benefits of the Fablabs network;
Allow FabLabs to come together to pool resources and equipment and develop joint projects.
However, none of the actions carried out within the framework of the aforementioned missions can justify interference in the internal functioning of its members.

Learn — Learn
Fabricate — Make
Share — Share


